Title : Bond Sound
Text : '''Bond Sound''' is a [[sound (geography)|sound]] located on the northeast side of [[Tribune Channel]] in the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast region]] of [[British Columbia]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/23656.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Bond Sound"]</ref>  Bond Sound, with the head of [[Kingcome Inlet]] to its north, frames the [[Wishart Peninsula]].  Like other names in the area, it was named by [[Daniel Pender|Captain Pender]] in 1865, in association with other names in the area associated with {{HMS|Tribune|1865|6}}.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/23656.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Bond Sound"]</ref>

[[Ahta Indian Reserve No. 3]] is located at the sound's northeast corner, at the mouth of the [[Ahta River]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/65363.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Ahta 3 (Indian reserve)"]</ref>

To the west of Bond Sound, on the same side of Tribune Channel, is [[Kwatsi Bay]].

